## What Changed

Minder's Realizer module now implements a complete hypothesis-first ideation loop:

1. **Capture** ‚Äî POST /api/realizer/hypothesis (title, value_path, candidate_spokes, urgency, opportunity_type)
2. **Identify** ‚Äî GET /api/realizer/hypothesis/{id}/affected_spokes ‚Äî keyword scorer ranks spokes by relevance
3. **Ground** ‚Äî POST /api/realizer/hypothesis/{id}/ground ‚Äî runs H1 (relevance) + H2 (active conflict) checks against top 3 candidate spokes
4. **Plan** ‚Äî POST /api/realizer/hypothesis/{id}/generate_plan ‚Äî Gemini 2.0-flash drafts 2-4 phased plan; stub fallback when no API key
5. **Dispatch** ‚Äî POST /api/realizer/hypothesis/{id}/dispatch/{phase_num} ‚Äî builds PEV-complete task lug, writes to spoke inbox

Feature-class lugs go to pending_dispatch (user approval required). Remediation lugs auto-confirm.

## Why It Matters

This closes the "idea ‚Üí implementation" loop that was missing from Realizer v1. Previously Realizer was observational (interrogate + gap dispatch). Now it can take a vague idea, ground it against spoke readiness, generate a phased plan, and dispatch buildable work directly into a spoke's inbox.

## Files

- `web/realizer_hypothesis.py` ‚Äî HypothesisStore, generate_hypothesis_id
- `web/realizer_plans.py` ‚Äî PlanStore, generate_draft_plan
- `web/realizer_dispatch.py` ‚Äî generate_hypothesis_lug, DECISION_CLASSES, classify_lug
- `web/realizer.py` ‚Äî identify_affected_spokes, interrogate_spoke(hypothesis=)
- `web/routes_realizer.py` ‚Äî 7 new endpoints
- `web/templates/realizer.html` ‚Äî Hypotheses panel with full UI

## Prerequisites

None ‚Äî Realizer must already be installed (Minder S60+)

